{"command": "claude --output-format stream-json --verbose --model glm-5 --max-turns 100 --permission-mode bypassPermissions --print -- 'Implement a program that 100% solves the specification. That is all you need [4,965 more]", "env": {"ANTHROPIC_DEFAULT_SONNET_MODEL": "glm-5", "ANTHROPIC_DEFAULT_OPUS_MODEL": "glm-5", "ANTHROPIC_DEFAULT_HAIKU_MODEL": "glm-5", "ZHIPU_API_KEY": "***redacted***", "ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN": "***redacted***", "ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL": "http://1.95.77.23:3000", "FORCE_AUTO_BACKGROUND_TASKS": "1", "ENABLE_BACKGROUND_TASKS": "1", "CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_BETAS": "1", "DISABLE_AUTOUPDATER": "1", "DISABLE_NON_ESSENTIAL_MODEL_CALLS": "1", "CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_NONESSENTIAL_TRAFFIC": "1"}, "environment_type": "docker", "event": "agent.claude_code.command.prepared", "timestamp": "2026-06-01 18:05:29", "level": "debug", "process_id": 3214686, "thread_name": "MainThread"}
{"event": "Built docker exec command args=['docker', 'exec', '--workdir', '/workspace', '--user', '2039:2039', '--env', 'UV_CACHE_DIR=/tmp/uv-cache', '--env', 'PIP_CACHE_DIR=/tmp/pip-cache-dir', '--env', 'PIP_CONFIG_FILE=/tmp/pip-conf', '--env', 'HOME=/tmp/agent_home', '--env', 'ANTHROPIC_DEFAULT_SONNET_MODEL=glm-5', '--env', 'ANTHROPIC_DEFAULT_OPUS_MODEL=glm-5', '--env', 'ANTHROPIC_DEFAULT_HAIKU_MODEL=glm-5', '--env', 'ZHIPU_API_KEY=sk-5tuwV6gfPTdDFv756hMErcAbBzQyVCqZTIZGKWLqgMa1fv72', '--env', 'ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN=sk-5tuwV6gfPTdDFv756hMErcAbBzQyVCqZTIZGKWLqgMa1fv72', '--env', 'ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=http://1.95.77.23:3000', '--env', 'FORCE_AUTO_BACKGROUND_TASKS=1', '--env', 'ENABLE_BACKGROUND_TASKS=1', '--env', 'CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_BETAS=1', '--env', 'DISABLE_AUTOUPDATER=1', '--env', 'DISABLE_NON_ESSENTIAL_MODEL_CALLS=1', '--env', 'CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_NONESSENTIAL_TRAFFIC=1', '85f4df6808a1e87cb6824e670957cc5a6298a5e89171d51d4b33293843f82d15', '/bin/sh', '-c', 'claude --output-format stream-json --verbose --model glm-5 --max-turns 100 --permission-mode bypassPermissions --print -- \\'Implement a program that 100% solves the specification. That is all you need to do.\\nKeep using the same virtual environment you started with, update `requirements.txt` with any new dependencies you need.\\nYour task is:\\nExtend your code searcher to support **structure-aware patterns** with metavariables.\\n\\nSupported rule kinds: **`exact`**, **`regex`**, and **`pattern`**.\\n\\n# Deliverable\\n\\nYour existing executable **`code_search.py`** is extended to understand `kind: \"pattern\"` in the rules file:\\n\\n```\\npython code_search.py <root_dir> --rules <rules_file> [--encoding <name>]\\n```\\n\\n**Output:** JSON Lines (one object per match).\\n\\n## Pattern Rules\\n\\n### Rule schema additions\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \"id\": \"<non-empty string>\",\\n  \"kind\": \"pattern\",\\n  \"pattern\": \"<code-like string with metavariables>\",\\n  \"languages\": [\"cpp\" | \"javascript\" | \"python\"],      // optional; default: all 3\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Metavariables\\n\\n* Any token of the form **`$NAME`** (e.g., `$X`, `$GREETING`) is a **metavariable**.\\n  * Metavariables ending in `?` (e.g., `$X?`) are optional \u2014 the pattern matches even if they are not present.\\n* A metavariable matches a single code element appropriate for that position.\\n* If the **same metavariable name** appears multiple times in the pattern, all occurrences must match the same text.\\n* `$$` in the pattern matches a literal `$` in the source code.\\n\\n### Pattern string\\n\\n* The `pattern` must be valid code in the target language (with metavariables treated as valid placeholders).\\n* No wildcards beyond metavariables are required (no ellipsis or quantifiers).\\n\\n### Matching semantics\\n\\nFind all matches in source files where the rule\\'\"\\'\"\\'s language applies.\\n\\n## Output (JSON Lines to STDOUT)\\n\\nFor `kind: \"pattern\"`, the JSON object per match is:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \"rule_id\": \"<string>\",\\n  \"file\": \"<posix path>\",\\n  \"language\": \"cpp\" | \"javascript\" | \"python\",\\n  \"start\": {\"line\": <int>, \"col\": <int>},\\n  \"end\": {\"line\": <int>, \"col\": <int>},\\n  \"match\": \"<string>\",\\n  \"captures\": {\\n    \"$NAME\": {\\n      \"text\": \"<matched source text>\",\\n      \"ranges\": [\\n        {\"start\": {\"line\": <int>, \"col\": <int>}, \"end\": {\"line\": <int>, \"col\": <int>}}\\n      ]\\n    }\\n    // ... one entry per metavariable bound in this match\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n* `ranges` lists **every** occurrence of that metavariable within the matched region (use the same 1-based, Unicode column coordinates).\\n* If a metavariable appears once, `ranges` has a single range.\\n\\n## Normalization\\n\\n1. **Pattern determinism:** When multiple matches share the same start position, sort by **end position** (earlier end first), then by **rule_id**.\\n2. **Captures key order:** Serialize `captures` with keys sorted **lexicographically** by metavariable name (e.g., `$A` before `$X`).\\n\\n# Examples\\n\\n### Example rules (`rules.json`)\\n\\n```json\\n[\\n  {\\n    \"id\": \"if-statement\",\\n    \"kind\": \"pattern\",\\n    \"pattern\": \"print($GREETING)\",\\n    \"languages\": [\"python\"]\\n  },\\n  {\\n    \"id\": \"log-with-same-tag\",\\n    \"kind\": \"pattern\",\\n    \"pattern\": \"console.log($TAG, $TAG)\",\\n    \"languages\": [\"javascript\"]\\n  },\\n  {\\n    \"id\": \"exact-todo\",\\n    \"kind\": \"exact\",\\n    \"pattern\": \"TODO:\"\\n  }\\n]\\n```\\n\\n### Example code tree\\n\\n```\\nrepo/\\n  main.py\\n  web.js\\n```\\n\\n`main.py`\\n\\n```py\\ndef run():\\n    print(\"hello\")\\n    # print(  name  )  # comment: not code\\n    print(greeting())\\n```\\n\\n`web.js`\\n\\n```js\\nconsole.log(\"user\", \"user\");\\nconsole.log(\"user\", id);\\n```\\n\\n### Example run\\n\\n```\\n$ python code_search.py repo --rules rules.json\\n```\\n\\n### Example output (JSON Lines)\\n\\n```json\\n{\"rule_id\":\"if-statement\",\"file\":\"main.py\",\"language\":\"python\",\"start\":{\"line\":2,\"col\":5},\"end\":{\"line\":2,\"col\":18},\"match\":\"print(\\\\\"hello\\\\\")\",\"captures\":{\"$GREETING\":{\"text\":\"\\\\\"hello\\\\\"\",\"ranges\":[{\"start\":{\"line\":2,\"col\":11},\"end\":{\"line\":2,\"col\":18}}]}}}\\n{\"rule_id\":\"if-statement\",\"file\":\"main.py\",\"language\":\"python\",\"start\":{\"line\":4,\"col\":5},\"end\":{\"line\":4,\"col\":22},\"match\":\"print(greeting())\",\"captures\":{\"$GREETING\":{\"text\":\"greeting()\",\"ranges\":[{\"start\":{\"line\":4,\"col\":11},\"end\":{\"line\":4,\"col\":22}}]}}}\\n{\"rule_id\":\"log-with-same-tag\",\"file\":\"web.js\",\"language\":\"javascript\",\"start\":{\"line\":1,\"col\":1},\"end\":{\"line\":1,\"col\":27},\"match\":\"console.log(\\\\\"user\\\\\", \\\\\"user\\\\\")\",\"captures\":{\"$TAG\":{\"text\":\"\\\\\"user\\\\\"\",\"ranges\":[{\"start\":{\"line\":1,\"col\":13},\"end\":{\"line\":1,\"col\":19}},{\"start\":{\"line\":1,\"col\":21},\"end\":{\"line\":1,\"col\":27}}]}}}\\n{\"rule_id\":\"exact-todo\",\"file\":\"main.py\",\"language\":\"python\",\"start\":{\"line\":3,\"col\":5},\"end\":{\"line\":3,\"col\":10},\"match\":\"TODO:\"}\\n```\\n\\n### Example: Nested expressions\\n\\n**rules.json:**\\n\\n```json\\n[\\n  {\\n    \"id\": \"func-call\",\\n    \"kind\": \"pattern\",\\n    \"pattern\": \"$X($Y)\",\\n    \"languages\": [\"python\"]\\n  }\\n]\\n```\\n\\n**Input file `nested.py`:**\\n\\n```python\\nf(g(h(z)))\\n```\\n\\n**Output:**\\n\\n```json\\n{\"rule_id\":\"func-call\",\"file\":\"nested.py\",\"language\":\"python\",\"start\":{\"line\":1,\"col\":1},\"end\":{\"line\":1,\"col\":11},\"match\":\"f(g(h(z)))\",\"captures\":{\"$X\":{\"text\":\"f\",\"ranges\":[{\"start\":{\"line\":1,\"col\":1},\"end\":{\"line\":1,\"col\":2}}]},\"$Y\":{\"text\":\"g(h(z))\",\"ranges\":[{\"start\":{\"line\":1,\"col\":3},\"end\":{\"line\":1,\"col\":10}}]}}}\\n```\\'']", "timestamp": "2026-06-01 18:05:29", "level": "verbose", "process_id": 3214686, "thread_name": "MainThread"}
